text: Black CID after bus rest and immediate departure with RFK - Focus: Cold Boot
title:
platform (e.g. BBG, FAT, TSP, Simulation,...):
FIT U11 PHEV
observed behaviour occurs on multiple platforms (yes/no):
NO
observed behaviour occurs in multiple lifecycles (yes/no):
NO
preconditions and actions (e.g. coding, route-url for navigation errors, weather/environmental circumstances):

Customer park his car. But he has to move his vehicle quickly. He gets in without waiting for the IDC to start up and drives backwards.
Customer is main user and a linked to the profile digital key ( IPhone and apple watch ) is installed and by the driver.

expected result/behaviour:

No Black CID after leaving RFK ( Early video )

observed result/behaviour:

RFK ist starting up in CID and the early video is displayed when he moves backwards.
Driver stop and drive forward ( Early video is also displayed ) after some seconds the early video is not longer displayed and the CID goes black.
After 13 seconds the CID start up, while starting to install the profile the CID goes shortly black again. After this the CID start correctly up and is usable.

possible impact:

Customer upset, can not use the system

actions/steps to recover from error:

Nothing, self healing

test case reference:
**Head Unit:** MGU_02_A; BMW IDC23;pu2411-24w25.7-2-nodex_IDC23_H_24w25.4-1-3-nodex_IDC23_H_24w25.4-1-3;idc23;HWEL:7D84-005.002.001

title:
*platform (e.g. BBG, FAT, TSP, Simulation,...)**:*

U12 production vehicle.

*observed behaviour occurs on multiple platforms (yes/no):*

As of the time the problem was reported, the behaviour of the problem has only been observed on a single platform(vehicle). But it doesn't mean the issue will never be reproduced on other platforms (vehicles). Also, there is a potential possibility that the failure mode of the behaviour of the problem was not effectively triggered on other platforms (vehicles), or that the problem was not noticed by the driver, so it was mistaken that the observed behaviour only occurs on a single platform (vehicle).

*observed behaviour occurs in multiple lifecycles (yes/no):*

As of the time the problem was reported, the behaviour of the problem has only been observed on a single lifecycle. But it doesn't mean the issue will never be reproduced on other lifecycles. Also, there is a potential possibility that the failure mode of the behaviour of the problem was not effectively triggered on other lifecycles, or that the problem was not noticed by the driver, so it was mistaken that the observed behaviour only occurs on a single lifecycle.

text: No Shutdown and Start with Active Screen after LC
title:
Platform (e.g. BBG, FAT, TSP, Simulation,...):

Vehicle with G070-24-03-540

Observed behavior occurs on multiple platforms (yes/no):

Inconclusive - In this testautomation run only one car was under test.

Observed behavior occurs in multiple lifecycles (yes/no):

23 events in 153 lifecycles

Test setup:
* Vehicle battery is supported
* A Breakoutbox is connected to the driver door plug.
* Therefore door contact signal (TK_VFA) can be controlled from external pc.
* Keyfob placed inside the car.

Test steps:

1. Vehicle is in PWF Parken

2. Start webcam recording

3. Send Signal DOOR OPEN for 5 seconds

4. Vehicle therefore goes into PWF Wohnen and IuK subsystem wakes up

5. Wait until IuK subsystem startup procedure is finished

6. Wait until car goes into PWF Parken due to timeout

7. Wait 1s - 15 min to simulate a short stop

8. Repeat with step 1

Expected result/behavior:

CID and IC Display are active within a reasonable time. Our soft boundary is 10s.

Observed result/behavior:
IC is starting direct after opening the door. CID is app 8sec delayed when this behaviour starts. IC and CID are not shutting down within 3:30 sec
after waiting app 6 min before next opening door both displays are still active.

Possible impact:

Customer is irritated and goes to the dealer.

actions/steps to recover from error:

recovering after 1 to 3 Cycle

text: [IDC23][STR] APIX MB0 Incorrect Configuration
title: During STR power state, the HUD MB0 pin is in the incorrect state. It is high and should be low. Also it was found in the normal state that is being driven high. This causes an odd voltage in normal operation. In normal operation it should be a pull up and not driven.

text: [IDC23][STR] APIX Chip Selects Incorrect in STR State
title:
During STR power state, the following APIX SPI chip selects are high. They must be low in STR state to avoid a backfeed path:_x005F_x000D_
_x005F_x000D_
HUD_CS1_x005F_x000D_
HUD_CS0_x005F_x000D_
_x005F_x000D_
DFE_CS1

text: [IDC23][STR] HUD_RESET_3.3V Incorrect in STR State
title:
During STR power state, HUD_RESET_3.3V is held high. It should be low. This will cause backfeed current through the APIX transceiver._x005F_x000D_
_x005F_x000D_

title:

-

*preconditions (e.g. coding, route-url for navigation errors, weather/environmental circumstances):*

Die folgenden DTCs wurden im Fahrzeug G000056 (J01) eingetragen:

The following DTCs occurred in the vehicle G000056 (J01):

0xE1D5E1 - Botschaft (Field displayArrows, 0x3509) nicht aktuell, EmpfÃ¤nger KOMBI, Sender BCP21_GW

0xE1D5E7 - Botschaft (Field displayStoppingFunction, 0x3509) nicht aktuell, EmpfÃ¤nger KOMBI, Sender BCP21_GW

The signals displayArrows, displayStoppingFunction are included in the PDU: DisplayDriverAssistanceLateralCoordinated

IB_VIP --> FAS_CAN_FD --> BCP21_GW --> Ethernet --> MGU

According to Carmen Preanalysis:

PWF Status: Driving

Speed: 0km/h

CCM: 914

At the time of the error there is a gap in the mentioned signals in Ethernet for about 5seconds. So, the 2 DTCs seems to be justified from MGU side.

However, during the time of the gap, VIP is sending the messages through FAS_CAN_FD to BCP21_GW. It seems that BCP for some reason does not send those messages during this time.

The purpose of this Ticket is to clarify why BCP does not send the messages.
